05/06/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Presidents Georgi Parvanov of Bulgaria, Ion Iliescu of Romania and Ahmet Necdet Sezer of Turkey said Wednesday (4 June) that they hope the EU will discuss their country's bids for membership at its summit on 21 June.
The statement came at the end of a two-day meeting in the Romanian town of Neptun.
The three called on EU leaders to confirm the accession of Bulgaria and Romania in 2007 and to discuss Turkey's future in the Union.
The presidents also pledged to fight terrorism and to boost economic co-operation between their countries.
(AFP, BNT, bTV - 04/06/03)
